the second version requires a certain intonation. Probably with a rising intonation at the end of the first conjunct, and a fall after the second.
Within the context, if it is appropriate for the speaker to have a pretence of ignorance, the version with -oo can be felicitous.
There is a contrast between -oo and -ainaa in such a context: -oo is better than -ainaa.
